Spring Boot : it is a java fraemwork used to build standalone ,production
 ready backend application quickly with minimal configuration.

 spring boot=Java+Ready made backend setup+less confuiguration
 why do we use it:
 To build REST APIs
 to connect to database
 create backend for apps/websites

THE THREE main Components of Spring Boot are:
1.Controller:handles incoming HTTP requests and returns response.
2.Service: service contains business logic(actual work of application).
3.Repository: Repository interacts with the data base (CRUD operations).

service-repository-database

Full Flow:
Client (Browser/Postman)
        ↓
Controller
        ↓
Service
        ↓
Repository
        ↓
Database


Spring boot contains a Container  called ioc:
IOC works to manage objects and create and also maintain the lifecycle of the objects
the objects is created and get called here in springboot
It also handles the dependency injection in spring